events.event_name: S&P Global Australia Services PMI Release
events.description: Final readings for the Australia Services PMI Business Activity Index for January.

facts.fact_text: The S&P Global Australia Services PMI Business Activity Index rose to 56.3 in January from 51.1 in December.

evidences.evidence_text: The S&P Global Australia Services PMI Business Activity Index rose to 56.3 in January from 51.1 in December

facts.fact_text: New orders rose at the fastest pace since April 2022.

evidences.evidence_text: new orders rising at the fastest pace since April 2022

facts.fact_text: Selling price inflation fell to a two-month low in January.

evidences.evidence_text: selling price inflation also softened and fell to a two-month low

claims.claim_text: The service sector expansion in January was the sharpest acceleration in nearly four years.
claims.author: S&P Global

evidences.evidence_text: indicating the sharpest acceleration in service sector expansion in nearly four years, according to final readings

claims.claim_text: Business confidence declined due to concerns over the economic outlook and competition.
claims.author: S&P Global

evidences.evidence_text: Business confidence, however, declined in January amid concerns over the economic outlook and competition

evidence.evidence_text: indicating the sharpest acceleration in service sector expansion in nearly four years
Employment increased at a solid and faster pace as firms hired to cope with heavier workloads
On the cost side, input price inflation eased despite ongoing wage and supply cost pressures
